      "text": "My idea is that why dont we just use all_users table\njoin dim customer still to get some details so we have live table. if\nnot all_users then base table which is \nauth_signups table. We don't need to check region for the new users\nthat's ok. \n\nthen we join braze customer table. if the braze customer table has\nthe user then apply the filters fair and square if they dont have\nthe user then just add them anyway because they might be\nsubscribed.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "My idea is that why dont we just use all_users table\njoin dim customer still to get some details so we have live table. if not all_users then base table which is \nauth_signups table. We don't need to check region for the new users that's ok. \n\nthen we join braze customer table. if the braze customer table has the user then apply the filters fair and square if they dont have the user then just add them anyway because they might be subscribed.\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
